On .NET 10, **you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was the .NET 9 workaround to make `dotnet test` talk to MTP. .NET 10 has native support â€” you just declare the runner in `global.json`.

Here's what to do:

**1. Remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from your csproj:**

```xml
<!-- DELETE this line -->
<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>
```

**2. Add a `test` section to `global.json`:**

```json
{
  "sdk": {
    "version": "10.0.100"
  },
  "test": {
    "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform"
  }
}
```

This tells `dotnet test` to use MTP natively â€” no `--` separator needed for MTP args (e.g., `dotnet test --report-trx` works directly).

